snippet.title: Inside Out 2 | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
üö®make room for new emotionsüö®

Watch the new trailer for Disney & Pixar's Inside Out 2, only in theaters June 14! #Insideout2 

The little voices inside Riley‚Äôs head know her inside and out‚Äîbut next summer, everything changes when Disney and Pixar‚Äôs ‚ÄúInside Out 2‚Äù introduces a new Emotion: Anxiety. According to director Kelsey Mann, the new character promises to stir things up within headquarters. ‚ÄúAnxiety, voiced by Maya Hawke, might be new to the crew, but she‚Äôs not really the type to take a back seat,‚Äù said Mann. ‚ÄúThat makes a lot of sense if you think about it in terms of what goes on inside all our minds.‚Äù A trailer, poster and film stills are now available for what promises to be the feel-good (or feel-everything) film of Summer 2024.
 
Disney and Pixar‚Äôs ‚ÄúInside Out 2‚Äù returns to the mind of newly minted teenager Riley just as headquarters is undergoing a sudden demolition to make room for something entirely unexpected: new Emotions! Joy, Sadness, Anger, Fear and Disgust, who‚Äôve long been running a successful operation by all accounts, aren‚Äôt sure how to feel when Anxiety shows up. And it looks like she‚Äôs not alone. Maya Hawke lends her voice to Anxiety, alongside Amy Poehler as Joy, Phyllis Smith as Sadness, Lewis Black as Anger, Tony Hale as Fear, and Liza Lapira as Disgust. Directed by Kelsey Mann and produced by Mark Nielsen, ‚ÄúInside Out 2‚Äù releases only in theaters Summer 2024.
